       }\\n\\n        public AlphaPeer getPeer() {\\n            return peer;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static final class AlphaPeer {\\n        private float alpha = 1.0f;\\n\\n        public void setAlpha(float alpha) {\\n            this.alpha = alpha;\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}\n2464:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering Native Image Issues**\\n\\nI’m exploring the potential of constructing a window with a Linux OS and how this interacts with Mac settings. There’s a concern about class loading and JUnit imports, as well as the Native Image issue where classes might initialize at build time, which could ignore runtime properties. I’m considering adding a properties file to control initialization, but I’m cautious about possible breaks in functionality. I need to weigh the necessity of this change carefully.\\n\\n**Examining Class Initialization**\\n\\nI believe classes typically initialize at runtime, except for some from the JDK that might initialize early due to analysis. I need to consider whether I should reset `WindowUtils.Holder`, especially if the test order impacts its state. It's unclear if a placeholder is needed, but it seems unnecessary to remove it. I might need to create a dedicated file for dynamic-access classes, as the existing placeholder doesn't seem relevant anymore.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_019e8a5ce0c495eb0169f8c8a1f740819488234765e5e075f0\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-MiyZQWlZD3LvgSkKQgJo1hVcP9kNEAoaeD9GnhtaW3XeH-HSCoOJtdPebDJtFejOiYdCiWyqhXqhRhQY1RzMPmBotD5T8Jue9Xj-kbzumUYJR6vA4C_Q4nDiO6wkvu9eTGxEUt5J6burp5Ps7XoYA08KMxo9HxpdfIMJynaB3UfaVsHQrZMWh3Tyq793mG3MDVRB1MYEPLiUahEnmH9BD94AsoM898At0diFylzgt_W0RGq1P42QhD0kbd1b2RGEz8_D17YoRTiYe9m1FCxNhC3t3pv5VSrYT4bn_DaKMsRyloMaEUxAN4-LSxtVqk16jeHpyyu-2s6P_xyGAsjNzeIOWriNjmiR3IYzzU7apJJkBGtkLKIAj2BUsl6RVCHUlwPRvz9GWMHtxOr7LK