etPeer` method and determining if it can return a peer class where `setAlpha` exists. The object must extend `Window` and have a public `getPeer`. I'm also thinking about using dynamic proxies, but that might not fit well. The AWT old implementation doesn't seem suitable, and using a class from the library might need a custom subclass test. I wonder if the `@RegisterForReflection` annotation would help—time to check my dependencies!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_019e8a5ce0c495eb0169f8c88eb06c81948d2578670b29b406\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-MiehYQMsbKGG2SsDenmC-QN0JD6JhVc92xJmahJb4ez3JxmbTcjKKqi99OPcKxo5taTgCB0SIvjjh7cb9zSHA4k_qOpk-JZuveVs6YiNJ60KBKhuGOw32LmyAjkKZnOrPvKpsJgtP9muWcx94X7D59ZtGvAcm-zPikxs1nTLVfjhD79rLoBsvASj4cSjpQzEC4bJ45zN5ZpCREvU65d3rwbIqwNkztPcZfZ7agP_evdw6nS2aatRpjEludbrcL-vMOYfL3upxh8C4m3QbPt3vtA1kNKbrdQCZXcz-wYQ9qoAikKeS9rwLSyXemoR4NuDor6WH3H9s5g_ymVIYsDR-x6xbTM7kxNeHYcBmA6HMqivFASdbV6gov_PuW3su9SfSvXvc8oV3_PvOBlWIHcPr1YArHvgCeb7-VNWgv8x6XOuraFVt9lbY5i0VUZpyne9lHzFeRHfJzJNK7GsmbGFoWdY6yAAWrvmM_2XcWAtG2mZyt3DEAVFn9W2HEEOI79AHWtNcsvnLf8D-P8KE7RLQK-LA3pWyxyxXQ9Kc_1qKt7FYt3bWlqIii2pH8l2g7g-DQpLO054avYD1FkuqYLaW5g1fx2FawnmCVjL7QMBkTHMAqEmddFaZC22ZK_i5avXcc6rxmJCeOq2_ySpH9UPdA31PAhDVxUkfXEdq4_19P8IR7tMaKgos_VivUvukF354UKa2rknvyN2UULF75GsdVUUzYmgqm-fzr16EGAhbXii-P9toOQMcVvyR-SemhVZYCszE7ZmEbSDNrlYz9ZlaO1bK9QNQVG-2Ql_-RL8z6y2F8f6drhLZtxD_OHFdR5aO--7F4v31vaj0Mi-oLp5XxdlnrKOrFHFPisgBRTAkHZ6WH5fJGs9NXQJuMiWLgOEzDmMpJT2Q_lgOJqwatYyxnSAUKwKjD51X4Z__AAOmshvtgT131qJmoWc2_N5HIwfbrmDudy1Eif8fe6eH1iUugv53f-1hpfLACA0mbp29jn7WQqM-wjPfdvn0_ijW1Iw7VtmQDBkRTT_-rpe4Seg1_MykXD2ObJUJVvKf7V6QBmr65Vhb9bTMTctl9Ah3h63QN8xxOfnEKly-k0gH1KZUneWaDa8oWAlCO_kFyt9nTO3H1e1j8Aqzbdmh61uQDJ53hr1gVGwwbjF2tO3JTW6iSBw9NpuA9Kuap_Gry9hYKVZo9y4lX7pQsE6hOXO0K_ZxEi7AF5KSc8m54-PDqWL2rbl8KSoR3AsyPyWVc4SUzHq9CFvhekS9smWxchdRh6cHvKKWIlFTel1k3UGN45hZ0jQXzfbw5pNC_yPgG97zhHXTxO6goQKHP0VQh0D7BgE2-sibfDLY3tsWTD47G0F2BM_ylD7qaM9gaIiTxh-JppiI7y